5.7 Given cumulative emissions and population figures, global annual average 
per capita carbon emissions can be derived. As an illustration, for the median 
UN population projections, the future average annual per capita use of fossil 
fuel cannot much exceed the current global average if the atmospheric 
concentration of carbon dioxide is to remain below 550 ppmv. Annual average 
per capita emissions would be higher for stabilization levels above 750 ppmv, 
but still less than 2 tonnes. 


